# PDF fixtures are byte-exact: their xref tables store absolute byte offsets,
# so any line-ending translation corrupts them. The hand-built example form
# contains no NUL bytes, so git's text heuristic would otherwise CRLF-convert
# it on Windows checkouts (caused a Windows-only e2e failure).
*.pdf binary

# FDF is plain text that ffpdf reads byte-wise; keep it diffable but never
# translated.
*.fdf -text
